Key Match Events: Ryan O'Hearn and Colton Cowser homered for the Baltimore Orioles as they defeated the Minnesota Twins 7-2.
Cade Povich pitched shutout ball into the sixth inning.
Ryan O’Hearn hit a two-run homer in the second inning.
Colton Cowser hit his 24th homer of the season in the seventh inning.
Carlos Santana hit a two-run single in the ninth inning for the Twins.
Post-Match Reflections: The Orioles wrapped up the top AL wild-card spot and will host either Detroit or Kansas City in the opening round next week.
The Twins were eliminated from postseason contention with this loss.
